whereas.text:
Whereas the social work profession has been instrumental
			 in achieving advances in civil and human rights in the United States and across
			 the world for more than a century;

Whereas the primary mission of social work is to enhance
			 human well-being and help meet the basic needs of all people, especially the
			 people who are most vulnerable;

Whereas the programs and services provided by professional
			 social workers are essential elements of the social safety net in the United
			 States;

Whereas social workers function as specialists,
			 consultants, private practitioners, educators, community leaders, policymakers,
			 and researchers;

Whereas social workers seek to improve social functioning
			 and social conditions for people in emotional, psychological, economic, or
			 physical need;

Whereas social workers believe that the strength of a
			 country depends on the ability of the majority of the people to lead productive
			 and healthy lives;

paragraph.text:
supports the
			 goals and ideals of Professional Social Work Month and World Social Work
			 Day;
